From: OctaneOS <octaneos@local>
Date: Wed, 09 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] sound: add MODULE_ALIAS to snd_sunxi_codec_av for udev auto-load

The sunxi-snd-codec-av platform device is created dynamically by the
DRM EDP driver during probe.  Without a MODULE_ALIAS the kernel's depmod
generates no alias for snd_sunxi_codec_av.ko, so udev never triggers
modprobe when the device appears.

The machine driver (i2s3_mach) references the codec via
sound-dai = <&edp0>; soc-core resolves it through the OF parent node
fallback (soc-core.c:806).  If snd_sunxi_codec_av is not loaded before
the machine driver probes, snd_soc_of_get_dai_link_codecs() returns
-EPROBE_DEFER forever → i2s3_mach never registers → aplay -l shows
"no soundcards found".

Add MODULE_ALIAS("platform:sunxi-snd-codec-av") so depmod creates the
platform alias and udev auto-loads the module when the EDP driver
creates the platform device.

---
 bsp/drivers/sound/platform/snd_sunxi_codec_av.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/bsp/drivers/sound/platform/snd_sunxi_codec_av.c b/bsp/drivers/sound/platform/snd_sunxi_codec_av.c
index aaaaaa1..bbbbbbb 100644
--- a/bsp/drivers/sound/platform/snd_sunxi_codec_av.c
+++ b/bsp/drivers/sound/platform/snd_sunxi_codec_av.c
@@ -271,3 +271,4 @@
 MODULE_LICENSE("GPL");
 MODULE_VERSION("1.0.0");
 MODULE_DESCRIPTION("sunxi soundcard codec of av");
+MODULE_ALIAS("platform:sunxi-snd-codec-av");
